First of all, some people are actually convinced that AD has every guide/GM in their back pockets.  Yes, it's true, we all send &quot;donations&quot; to them, and buy them to rule in favor of AD in any disagreement. We all have secret passes to cshome where we laugh about how we screw other guilds, no one knows about this because AD is always on /role and you cant see us there.  People try to label us as whiners because a GM shows up when 2 guilds are racing for a mob.  This is the funniest of all really.  Is it AD that whines on a R&amp;F board whenever the lose a spawn?  Is it AD that whines in the Triality public forum?  Is it AD's guild leader who cries, and claims that they will blow emp every time he is up so AD doesnt get to kill it? (funny...they say they will blow the spawn....do they lack the confidence that they can actually win?). Is it AD's guild leader who gets suspended after throwing a temper tantrum like a 2 year old after things dont go his way?  The answer to all the above questions is no. (the answer would be yes if I switched AD for Triality and vice versa) Despite this, people come here, and have the audacity to try and label us as whiners. Unbelievable.<br>
<br>
What are some other things I find quite humorous...<br>
<br>
Oh...this is good, accusing mandaar of dispelling statue.  Ok, let me get this straight, instead of healing (he is an AD cleric), he decides...hey...lets screw over my own guild...and dispell statue, to make it look like Triality did it.  In addition to intentionally trying to make AD lose, Mandaar also is so feeble minded that he declares in a public channel that he dispelled statue.  This really is your claim?...this is what you are trying to say? If in some twisted way, it really is, I truly pity anyone who would believe this.  Tell me if this sounds more logical.  We are killing statue.  Mandaar NOTICES that statue has been dispelled, and then broadcasts in a public channel &quot;statue has been dispelled&quot;, with the intention of INFORMING AD members to re-slow, debuff, etc..<br>
<br>
Oh...and Amato saying AD tried to KS..<br>
<br>
This is what he was referring to, Triality pulled Vindi and other mobs,  those mobs that Triality pulled eventually ended up in our camp (train...proven by the dead Triality member in the dead center of our camp), and we went ahead and tried to kill mobs pulled in the train.<br>
<br>
This too....why does AD kill AoW, are they so gimp they can't go after anything better?<br>
<br>
Well, I'll put it simply.  We get warrior applications, and these apps sometimes become members, now these warriors may not have an enraging blow weapon...hmm...where is an easy place to get a quick EB weapon...ah ha...AoW.  You see, we like to get all of our warriors geared up...not just one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . And, so what if AD kills a mob that isn't uber.  It's up, we want something off it, we kill it.  Period.<br>
<br>
Xerg<br>
<br>
